{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Customer Churn Prediction: Exploratory Data Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook analyzes the Telco Customer Churn dataset to uncover insights that might help in predicting churn. \n",
    "We will explore the data distribution, relationships between features and the target variable (`Churn`), and check for data quality."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set plotting style\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid')\n",
    "sns.set_palette('Set2')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load Data\n",
    "Let's load the dataset and take an initial look at its structure."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load data\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../data/WA_Fn-UseC_-Telco-Customer-Churn.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display basic info\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset Shape: {df.shape}\")\n",
    "display(df.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Data Cleaning and Optimization\n",
    "First, we'll fix issues with data types. The `TotalCharges` column seems to be inferred as an object due to blank spaces. We'll convert it to numeric and handle missing values."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Data Quality Check & Type Casting\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert TotalCharges to numeric, setting errors='coerce' to turn spaces into NaNs\n",
    "df['TotalCharges'] = pd.to_numeric(df['TotalCharges'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Missing values after conversion:\")\n",
    "print(df.isnull().sum())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fill NaNs with the median\n",
    "df['TotalCharges'].fillna(df['TotalCharges'].median(), inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Memory Optimization: Convert appropriate object columns to 'category' dtype\n",
    "cat_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns\n",
    "for col in cat_cols:\n",
    "    if col not in ['customerID', 'Churn']:\n",
    "        df[col] = df[col].astype('category')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nData info after optimization:\")\n",
    "print(df.info())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Exploratory Analysis\n",
    "Now we'll define a set of visualizations to better understand what drives customer churn."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(16, 12))\n",
    "fig.suptitle(\"Key Drivers of Customer Churn\", fontsize=16)\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1. Churn Distribution\n",
    "ax = sns.countplot(x='Churn', data=df, ax=axes[0, 0])\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_title('Overall Churn Distribution')\n",
    "for p in ax.patches:\n",
    "    ax.annotate(f'{p.get_height() / len(df):.1%}', \n",
    "                (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height() / 2.), \n",
    "                ha='center', va='center', fontsize=12, color='white', weight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Churn by Contract Type\n",
    "sns.countplot(x='Contract', hue='Churn', data=df, ax=axes[0, 1])\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_title('Churn by Contract Type')\n",
    "axes[0, 1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=15)\n",
    "\n",
    "# 3. Monthly Charges Distribution\n",
    "sns.kdeplot(data=df, x='MonthlyCharges', hue='Churn', common_norm=False, fill=True, ax=axes[1, 0])\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_title('Monthly Charges vs. Churn')\n",
    "\n",
    "# 4. Tenure vs Churn Rate\n",
    "# Calculate churn rate by tenure bin\n",
    "df['tenure_binned'] = pd.cut(df['tenure'], bins=10)\n",
    "churn_rate = df.groupby('tenure_binned')['Churn'].apply(lambda x: (x == 'Yes').mean()).reset_index()\n",
    "churn_rate['tenure_binned'] = churn_rate['tenure_binned'].astype(str)\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.barplot(x='tenure_binned', y='Churn', data=churn_rate, ax=axes[1, 1], color='steelblue')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_title('Churn Rate by Tenure')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_ylabel('Churn Rate')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.92)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Insights\n",
    "1. **Imbalance:** The dataset is imbalanced (~26.5% of customers churn). We should use techniques like `class_weight='balanced'` during model training.\n",
    "2. **Contracts:** Month-to-month contracts have a drastically higher churn rate than 1-year or 2-year contracts.\n",
    "3. **Pricing:** Higher Monthly Charges generally correlate with higher churn.\n",
    "4. **Tenure:** Newer customers (low tenure) are much more at risk of churning than long-term customers."
   ]
  }
 ],
